creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 128 by Various.
Read in English by volunteer readers.

This is a collection of 29 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for January 2014. The collection contains the following:

As I Came Down Mount Tamalpais by Clarence Urmy
Burbank with a Baedeker: Bleistein with a Cigar by T. S. Eliot
The Call of the Wild by Robert W. Service
A Clear Midnight by Walt Whitman
A Dream Within a Dream by Edgar Allan Poe
Finis by E. E. Cummings
A Health by Edward Coote Pinkney
I Remember by Thomas Hood
I Wandered Lonely as a Cloud by William Wordsworth
Invictus by William Ernest Henley
Life by Paul Laurence Dunbar
Lucille by Robert W. Service
A Melody by Scarlatti by Aldous Huxley
The Men that Don't Fit In by Robert W. Service
Mnemosyne by Trumbull Stickney
No! by Thomas Hood
November by William Cullen Bryant
Peace by Henry Vaughan
Retort by Paul Laurence Dunbar
Rivals by William Walsh
Silence by Thomas Hood
Sonnet 1 by Fernando Pessoa
Sweeney Among the Nightingales by T. S. Eliot
Sweeney Erect by T. S. Eliot
Symphony in Yellow by Oscar Wilde
There Was a Boy by William Wordsworth
To Autumn by William Blake
Which Are You? by Ella Wheeler Wilcox
Young and Old by Charles Kingsley


For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
